{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EAtU8KkiNmMiJcMMS91wCu","type":"tool_result","content":"   150→      content: `TAUNT lets you choose your own wager amount for every game.\n   151→\n   152→Wager limits:\n   153→• Minimum: 0.001 SOL\n   154→• Maximum: 100 SOL\n   155→\n   156→How it works:\n   157→• Enter any amount within the limits before joining a game\n   158→• In head-to-head games (Flip You), both players wager the same amount\n   159→• In pool games (Lord of RNGs, Close Call), your share of the pool scales with your wager\n   160→\n   161→Benefits:\n   162→• Play at exactly the stake you're comfortable with\n   163→• No fixed tiers — full flexibility\n   164→• Preset buttons for quick common amounts`\n   165→    },\n   166→    {\n   167→      id: \"leaderboard\",\n   168→      title: \"Leaderboard System\",\n   169→      content: `Leaderboard system details coming soon.\n   170→\n   171→We're working on implementing competitive leaderboards to track and reward top players. Stay tuned for updates!`\n   172→    },\n   173→    {\n   174→      id: \"fairness\",\n   175→      title: \"On-Chain Fairness\",\n   176→      content: `All game outcomes are provably fair using cryptographic verification:\n   177→\n   178→Commit-Reveal Pattern (Crash, Close Call):\n   179→1. Server publishes a hash of its seed before betting\n   180→2. Solana blockhash becomes the public seed\n   181→3. After the round, server reveals its seed\n   182→4. Anyone can verify the outcome matches\n   183→\n   184→On-Chain VRF (Jackpot, Flip You):\n   185→1. Game requests randomness from VRF provider\n   186→2. VRF generates verifiable random bytes\n   187→3. Result and proof stored on Solana blockchain\n   188→4. Anyone can verify using blockchain explorer\n   189→\n   190→Visit the Fairness page in the header for verification tools.`\n   191→    },\n   192→    {\n   193→      id: \"rng-buff\",\n   194→      title: \"Heater\",\n   195→      content: `The Heater is a powerful temporary bonus granted to players who help drop the Mark before the timer expires.\n   196→\n   197→How to get the Heater:\n   198→1. Participate in the hourly Dogpile Raid by wagering in any game\n   199→2. Your wagers land \"hits\" on the Mark\n   200→3. If the Mark is dropped before time runs out, ALL participants receive the Heater\n   201→4. The Heater lasts for 1 hour (until the next raid starts)\n   202→\n   203→Heater Benefits:\n   204→• Golden glowing border on your avatar (visible to all players)\n   205→• Chance to drop crates when wagering\n   206→• Drop chance scales with wager amount (1% base + 5% per SOL, max 25%)\n   207→\n   208→Visual Indicators:\n   209→• Golden pulsing border around your avatar everywhere in the app\n   210→• Heater icon with countdown timer in your profile header\n   211→• Star icon with timer in the main header\n   212→\n   213→The Heater expires when the next raid begins, so make the most of it!`\n   214→    },\n   215→    {\n   216→      id: \"treasure-chests\",\n   217→      title: \"Crates\",\n   218→      content: `Crates are mystery rewards that contain XP and SOL prizes. Open them in the Loot page.\n   219→\n   220→How to earn crates:\n   221→• Heater drops: Random chance when wagering with active Heater\n   222→• Complete ALL daily quests: 1 crate\n   223→• Complete weekly quests: 1 crate per quest (3 total)\n   224→• Complete ALL weekly quests: +2 bonus crates (5 total)\n   225→\n   226→Heater crate drop rates:\n   227→• Base chance: 1% per wager\n   228→• Bonus: +5% per 1 SOL wagered\n   229→• Maximum: 25% chance per wager\n   230→\n   231→Crate rarity (determined when opened):\n   232→• Common (50%): 50-100 XP, 0.001-0.005 SOL\n   233→• Uncommon (30%): 100-250 XP, 0.005-0.01 SOL\n   234→• Rare (15%): 250-500 XP, 0.01-0.025 SOL\n   235→• Epic (4%): 500-1000 XP, 0.025-0.05 SOL\n   236→• Legendary (1%): 1000-2500 XP, 0.05-0.1 SOL\n   237→\n   238→SOL rewards are paid from the platform treasury. May the RNG gods smile upon you!`\n   239→    },\n   240→  ];\n   241→\n   242→  return (\n   243→    <>\n   244→      <footer className=\"footer-v2\">\n   245→        <div className=\"ft-logo\">TAUNT<em>.</em></div>\n   246→        <div className=\"ft-links\">\n   247→          <button type=\"button\" className=\"ft-lnk\" onClick={() => setShowFAQ(true)}>FAQ</button>\n   248→          <button type=\"button\" className=\"ft-lnk\" onClick={() => setShowTerms(true)}>Terms</button>\n   249→          <a href=\"https://x.com/rngutopia\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" className=\"ft-lnk\">Twitter</a>\n   250→          <a href=\"https://t.me/rngutopia\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" className=\"ft-lnk\">Telegram</a>\n   251→        </div>\n   252→        <div className=\"ft-tag\">taunt.bet &middot; Provably Fair &middot; Solana</div>\n   253→      </footer>\n   254→\n   255→      {/* Terms Modal */}\n   256→      {showTerms && (\n   257→        <div className=\"footer-terms-overlay\">\n   258→          <div className=\"footer-terms-modal\" ref={termsModalRef}>\n   259→            <button\n   260→              type=\"button\"\n   261→              className=\"footer-terms-close\"\n   262→              onClick={() => setShowTerms(false)}\n   263→            >\n   264→              ×\n   265→            </button>\n   266→            <h3 className=\"footer-terms-title\">Terms of Use</h3>\n   267→            <div className=\"footer-terms-content\">\n   268→              <p>\n   269→                By accessing and using TAUNT, you confirm that you are not a citizen,\n   270→                resident, or located within any jurisdiction where online gambling is prohibited\n   271→                or restricted by law, including but not limited to: the United States,\n   272→                United Kingdom, France, Germany, Spain, the Netherlands, or any other\n   273→                jurisdiction with similar regulations.\n   274→              </p>\n   275→              <p>\n   276→                You are solely responsible for determining whether your use of this platform\n   277→                is lawful in your country or region of residence. TAUNT does not provide\n   278→                legal advice and assumes no liability for users who access the platform in\n   279→                violation of applicable laws.\n   280→              </p>\n   281→              <p>\n   282→                By continuing to use this service, you acknowledge and accept these terms.\n   283→              </p>\n   284→            </div>\n   285→            <button\n   286→              type=\"button\"\n   287→              className=\"footer-terms-accept\"\n   288→              onClick={() => setShowTerms(false)}\n   289→            >\n   290→              I Understand\n   291→            </button>\n   292→          </div>\n   293→        </div>\n   294→      )}\n   295→\n   296→      {/* FAQ Modal */}\n   297→      {showFAQ && (\n   298→        <div className=\"footer-faq-overlay\">\n   299→          <div className=\"footer-faq-modal\" ref={faqModalRef}>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011AcsGVUbbSU9Yvp6f64T82","session_id":"1c981b50-fe84-48cc-8274-9e2683b7ad2f","uuid":"3c53c3b1-992d-45b8-bb39-c8c17bdd296a","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:53:56.959Z"}
